Vercel Web Analytics Configuration Completed

## Summary
Successfully configured Vercel Web Analytics for the VoyageX Next.js project following the latest official documentation from Vercel.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:
- **app/layout.tsx** - Added Vercel Analytics component to the root layout

### Specific Changes:
1. Imported the Analytics component from '@vercel/analytics/next'
2. Added the <Analytics /> component at the end of the body section in the root layout

## Implementation Details

The project already had @vercel/analytics v2.0.1 installed in package.json, so no package installation was needed.

Following the official Vercel documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I:
- Identified this as a Next.js App Router project (Next.js 16.0.10)
- Added the Analytics component to the root layout (app/layout.tsx) following the App Router pattern
- Placed the component at the end of the body tag, after existing components (OfflineDetector and children)

## Verification Steps Completed

✅ Build test passed - The production build completed successfully with all 66 routes generated
✅ Linting check passed - No new linting errors introduced in the modified file
✅ Dependencies installed - npm install completed successfully
✅ Type checking passed - TypeScript compilation successful during build

## Next Steps for Deployment

To activate Web Analytics:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard for this project
2. Deploy the application using `vercel deploy`
3. Verify analytics are working by checking the Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*`

## Notes

- The Analytics component is now included in every page of the application via the root layout
- The component is lightweight and won't affect page performance
- Analytics data will start collecting once the project is deployed to Vercel and Analytics is enabled in the dashboard
- All existing functionality remains unchanged
